    "2022, Appendix A.5, for more details).",
    "These measurements may underestimate the true positional errors because of, e.g., calibration uncertainties and other systematic effects (e.g.",
    "Webb et al. 2020).",
    "In particular, the astrometric accuracy of the eROSITA all-sky catalogues can be affected by the following systematic factors:-Errors in the timing between attitude measurements and event arrival; -Boresight calibration errors; -Systematic errors introduced by the PSF fitting.",
